the same thing, as the example of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Kathie Lee Gifford</ENAMEX> will now demonstrate. A
few <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">months</TIMEX> back, you may remember, the infernally perky <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gifford</ENAMEX> got some bad
press when it turned out that some of her clothing line was produced in <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Central</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">American</ENAMEX> sweatshops employing <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">child</ENAMEX> labor. Since then she has had other
problems, which are more up <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bob Wright</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">alley</ENAMEX> than mine. But it is useful, as a thought
experiment, to ask how <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">opponents</ENAMEX> of imports would have reacted had the story
been slightly different.

            
